  "texts": [
    "This parallel processing allows for real-time detection in video streams by handling multiple frames concurrently [2,8].",
    "B. SSD (Single Shot Multibox Detector)SSD, or Single Shot MultiBox Detector, is an object detection technique optimized for a trade-off between accuracy and speed.",
    "It operates by employing a predefined set of boxes with various aspect ratios at each cell of the feature map.",
    "Simultaneously, it predicts both bounding box offsets and class scores.",
    "Let's see the working of SSD in detail:• Feature Extraction: The input image is fed into a base Convolutional Neural Network (CNN), often based on architectures like VGG16."
  ]
}